Diagram 1 (Mistake)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par It is a beginners' mistake for white to push in on the first line with 1.
\par
\par It is a good move for black to throw-in at 2. You might think it a pae but actually it isn't.
\par .
\par When white captures black at 3, if black plays dansu from the outside with 4, white is trapped unable to connect. Black is alive
\par }
