Diagram 2 (Calm)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par The enemy's key point is your own. So, what about white 1?
\par
\par It is a calm response for black to play 2, creating more eyespace. If white plays 3, black plays dansu at 4 and lives with a lot of points.
\par
\par \pard\ltrpar\nowidctlpar\qj Instead of 4, if black connects at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , the black group is dead due having a dead shape. Bent four in the corner.
\par }
