Diagram 3 (Creative)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White 1 is creative. However, when black plays at 2, white cannot create a completely dead shape, and merely adds extra stones as a sacrifice.
\par
\par When black captures white at 4, even if white makes one eye false with 5, black can resist at 6, starting a pae. It was a fantastically energetic attack, but in the end it fails.
\par
\par The reason it is classed as a failure is because in this case there is a way to capture black unconditionally.
\par }
